# Forui Design System (Direct Integration - 2025 Best Practices)

**Context:** You use the `forui` library directly. **Do NOT create generic wrapper widgets** (e.g., `AppButton`, `BaseCard`). Follow the 2025 standard patterns for optimal performance and maintainability.

## 1. Core Directives

* **Direct Imports:** Import `package:forui/forui.dart` in feature files.
* **No Wrappers:** Use `FButton`, `FCard`, `FScaffold` directly in your widget trees.
* **Theme Access:** Use `context.theme` to access colors, typography, and styles.
* **Material Compatibility:** Use `toApproximateMaterialTheme()` for Material widgets integration.

## 2. Application Setup (main.dart)

**CRITICAL:** Follow this exact pattern for root application setup:

```dart
import 'package:forui/forui.dart';
import 'package:pharma_scan/theme/theme.dart'; // Generated theme

class PharmaScanApp extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    final foruiTheme = greenLight; // or greenDark for dark mode
    
    return MaterialApp.router(
      // Material theme for Material widgets compatibility
      theme: foruiTheme.toApproximateMaterialTheme(),
      darkTheme: greenDark.toApproximateMaterialTheme(), // if dark mode supported
      
      // Forui localizations (REQUIRED)
      supportedLocales: FLocalizations.supportedLocales,
      localizationsDelegates: const [...FLocalizations.localizationsDelegates],
      
      // FAnimatedTheme MUST be in builder, not directly in MaterialApp
      builder: (context, child) => FAnimatedTheme(
        data: foruiTheme,
        child: child!,
      ),
      
      routerConfig: goRouter,
    );
  }
}
```

**Key Points:**

* `FAnimatedTheme` must be in the `builder` callback, not as a direct child
* Always include `FLocalizations` for proper widget localization
* Use `toApproximateMaterialTheme()` for Material widget compatibility
* Theme is animated by default (smooth transitions)

## 3. Scaffold Pattern

**Use `FScaffold` instead of Material `Scaffold`:**

```dart
FScaffold(
  header: FHeader(
    title: const Text('Page Title'),
    suffixes: [
      FHeaderAction(
        icon: const Icon(FIcons.settings),
        onPress: () {},
      ),
    ],
  ),
  child: YourContent(),
  footer: FBottomNavigationBar(
    index: currentIndex,
    onChange: (index) => onTabChanged(index),
    children: [
      FBottomNavigationBarItem(
        icon: const Icon(FIcons.house),
        label: const Text('Home'),
      ),
      // ... more items
    ],
  ),
)
```

**Nested Navigation:**

```dart
FScaffold(
  header: FHeader.nested(
    title: const Text('Detail View'),
    prefixes: [
      FHeaderAction.back(onPress: () => context.pop()),
    ],
    suffixes: [
      FHeaderAction(
        icon: const Icon(FIcons.info),
        onPress: () {},
      ),
    ],
  ),
  child: YourContent(),
)
```

**Important:** `FScaffold` automatically provides `FToaster` context for `showFToast`.

## 4. Toast Notifications

**Pattern:** Use `showFToast` (automatically works with `FScaffold`):

```dart
// ✅ Success Toast
showFToast(
  context: context,
  title: const Text('Success'),
  description: const Text('Operation completed'),
  icon: const Icon(FIcons.check),
);

// ✅ Error Toast
showFToast(
  context: context,
  title: const Text('Error'),
  description: const Text('Operation failed'),
  icon: const Icon(FIcons.triangleAlert),
);

// ✅ Toast with custom suffix button
showFToast(
  context: context,
  title: const Text('Download Complete'),
  description: const Text('Your file has been downloaded.'),
  suffixBuilder: (context, entry) => FButton.icon(
    onPress: () => entry.dismiss(),
    child: const Icon(FIcons.x),
  ),
);
```

**Key Points:**

* `showFToast` requires `FScaffold` context (provided automatically)
* Use `FIcons` for icons (from `forui_assets`)
* `suffixBuilder` receives `(context, entry)` - use `entry.dismiss()` to close

## 5. Dialog Pattern

**Pattern:** Use `showFDialog` with `FDialog` widget:

```dart
showFDialog(
  context: context,
  builder: (context, style, animation) => FDialog(
    style: style,
    animation: animation,
    title: const Text('Confirm Action'),
    body: const Text('This action cannot be undone.'),
    actions: [
      FButton(
        style: FButtonStyle.outline(),
        onPress: () => Navigator.of(context).pop(),
        child: const Text('Cancel'),
      ),
      FButton(
        style: FButtonStyle.destructive(),
        onPress: () {
          // Perform action
          Navigator.of(context).pop();
        },
        child: const Text('Confirm'),
      ),
    ],
  ),
);
```

**Key Points:**

* Builder receives `(context, style, animation)` - pass `style` and `animation` to `FDialog`
* `actions` is required (use empty list `[]` if no actions)
* Use `Navigator.of(context).pop()` to close

## 6. Sheet Pattern (Mobile/Desktop Adaptive)

**Pattern:** Use `showFSheet` for bottom sheets (mobile) or side sheets (desktop):

```dart
// Mobile: Bottom Sheet
showFSheet(
  context: context,
  side: FLayout.btt, // Bottom to Top
  barrierDismissible: true,
  draggable: true,
  builder: (context) => Padding(
    padding: const EdgeInsets.all(16),
    child: YourContent(),
  ),
);

// Desktop: Side Sheet
showFSheet(
  context: context,
  side: FLayout.ltr, // Left to Right
  builder: (context) => YourContent(),
);
```

**Key Points:**

* `FLayout.btt` for mobile bottom sheets
* `FLayout.ltr` or `FLayout.rtl` for desktop side sheets
* `draggable: true` enables swipe-to-dismiss on mobile

## 7. Controller Pattern (Hooks)

**Mandate:** Always use `forui_hooks` for component controllers.

```dart
import 'package:forui_hooks/forui_hooks.dart';
import 'package:flutter_hooks/flutter_hooks.dart';

// ✅ Accordion Controller
class MyWidget extends HookWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    final controller = useFAccordionController();
    return FAccordion(
      controller: controller,
      children: [
        FAccordionItem(
          title: const Text('Section 1'),
          child: const Text('Content'),
        ),
      ],
    );
  }
}

// ✅ Select Group Controller (Radio)
class SettingsWidget extends HookWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    final controller = useFSelectGroupController.radio();
    return FSelectGroup(
      controller: controller,
      children: [
        FRadio.grouped(
          value: 'option1',
          label: const Text('Option 1'),
        ),
      ],
    );
  }
}

// ✅ Select Controller (Dropdown)
class MySelectWidget extends HookWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    final controller = useFSelectController<String>();
    return FSelect(
      controller: controller,
      items: {
        'Option 1': 'value1',
        'Option 2': 'value2',
      },
      // ... other properties
    );
  }
}
```

**Available Hooks:**

* `useFAccordionController()` - For `FAccordion`
* `useFSelectGroupController.radio()` - For `FSelectGroup` with radio buttons
* `useFSelectController<T>()` - For `FSelect` dropdowns
* `useFPopoverController()` - For `FPopover`
* `useFTabController()` - For `FTabs`
* `useFPaginationController()` - For `FPagination`

## 8. Text Replacement Pattern

Replace `BaseText` with standard Flutter `Text` widget using theme typography:

```dart
// ❌ Old (Wrapper)
BaseText('Title', variant: TextVariant.h1)

// ✅ New (Direct)
Text('Title', style: context.theme.typography.h1)

// For muted text:
Text('Description', style: context.theme.typography.sm.copyWith(
  color: context.theme.colors.mutedForeground,
))
```

**Typography Mapping:**

* `h1` → `context.theme.typography.h1`
* `h2` → `context.theme.typography.h2`
* `h3` → `context.theme.typography.h3`
* `h4` → `context.theme.typography.h4` or `xl2`
* `body` → `context.theme.typography.base` or `p`
* `small` → `context.theme.typography.sm`
* `muted` → `context.theme.typography.sm.copyWith(color: context.theme.colors.mutedForeground)`

## 9. Button Replacement Pattern

```dart
// ❌ Old (Wrapper)
BaseButton(
  label: 'Click',
  variant: ButtonVariant.outline,
  onPressed: () {},
)

// ✅ New (Direct)
FButton(
  style: FButtonStyle.outline(),
  onPress: () {},
  child: const Text('Click'),
)

// With icon
FButton.icon(
  style: FButtonStyle.ghost(),
  onPress: () {},
  child: const Icon(FIcons.settings),
)
```

**Variant Mapping:**

* `primary` → Default `FButton(...)` or `FButtonStyle.primary()`
* `secondary` → `style: FButtonStyle.secondary()`
* `outline` → `style: FButtonStyle.outline()`
* `ghost` → `style: FButtonStyle.ghost()`
* `destructive` → `style: FButtonStyle.destructive()`

## 10. Card Replacement Pattern

```dart
// ❌ Old (Wrapper)
BaseCard(
  padding: EdgeInsets.all(16),
  child: ...,
)

// ✅ New (Direct) - For generic containers
FCard.raw(
  child: Padding(
    padding: const EdgeInsets.all(16),
    child: ...,
  ),
)

// ✅ New (Direct) - For cards with title/subtitle
FCard(
  title: const Text('Title'),
  subtitle: const Text('Subtitle'),
  child: ...,
)

// ✅ Custom styling
final customStyle = context.theme.cardStyle.copyWith(
  decoration: BoxDecoration(
    color: context.theme.colors.secondary.withValues(alpha: 0.08),
    border: Border.all(
      color: context.theme.colors.secondary.withValues(alpha: 0.2),
      width: 1.2,
    ),
  ),
);
FCard.raw(
  style: customStyle,
  child: ...,
)
```

## 11. Badge Replacement Pattern

```dart
// ❌ Old (Wrapper)
BaseBadge(
  label: 'Status',
  variant: BadgeVariant.outline,
)

// ✅ New (Direct)
FBadge(
  style: FBadgeStyle.outline(),
  child: const Text('Status'),
)

// Custom colored badge
FBadge(
  style: FBadgeStyle.primary().copyWith(
    color: context.theme.colors.primary,
    labelTextStyle: (state) => context.theme.typography.sm.copyWith(
      color: context.theme.colors.primaryForeground,
    ),
  ),
  child: const Text('Custom'),
)
```

**Badge Styles:**

* `FBadgeStyle.primary()` - Default filled badge
* `FBadgeStyle.secondary()` - Secondary color
* `FBadgeStyle.outline()` - Outlined badge
* `FBadgeStyle.destructive()` - Error/destructive badge

## 12. Input Field Pattern

```dart
// ✅ Standard Text Field
FTextField(
  label: const Text('Email'),
  hint: 'Enter your email',
  controller: emailController,
  keyboardType: TextInputType.emailAddress,
  prefixBuilder: (context, style, states) => const Icon(FIcons.mail),
  suffixBuilder: (context, style, states) => const Icon(FIcons.x),
)

// ✅ Form Field (with validation)
FTextFormField(
  controller: passwordController,
  label: const Text('Password'),
  hint: 'Enter password',
  validator: (value) => value?.isEmpty ?? true ? 'Required' : null,
  autovalidateMode: AutovalidateMode.onUserInteraction,
)

// ✅ Email Field (convenience constructor)
FTextFormField.email(
  controller: emailController,
  hint: 'john@doe.com',
  validator: (value) => value?.contains('@') ?? false ? null : 'Invalid email',
)

// ✅ Password Field (convenience constructor)
FTextFormField.password(
  controller: passwordController,
  obscureTextController: ValueNotifier(false), // For show/hide toggle
)
```

**Key Points:**

* Use `FTextField` for non-form inputs
* Use `FTextFormField` inside `Form` widgets
* `prefixBuilder` and `suffixBuilder` receive `(context, style, states)`
* Convenience constructors: `.email()`, `.password()`, `.multiline()`

## 13. Select/Dropdown Pattern

```dart
// ✅ Select with Controller (HookWidget)
class MySelectWidget extends HookWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    final controller = useFSelectController<String>();
    return FSelect(
      controller: controller,
      items: {
        'Option 1': 'value1',
        'Option 2': 'value2',
      },
      hint: 'Choose an option',
      onChange: (value) => print('Selected: $value'),
    );
  }
}

// ✅ Select.rich for custom item rendering
FSelect.rich(
  controller: controller,
  items: {
    'Option 1': 'value1',
    'Option 2': 'value2',
  },
  format: (value) => Text(value.toUpperCase()),
)
```

## 14. Alert Pattern

```dart
// ✅ Destructive Alert
FAlert(
  style: FAlertStyle.destructive(),
  icon: const Icon(FIcons.triangleAlert),
  title: const Text('Error'),
  subtitle: const Text('Something went wrong.'),
)

// ✅ Default Alert
FAlert(
